The paper discusses the development of safe AGI agents through value learning and ethical bias. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed extension of AIXI involves hierarchical value learning, which can be related to robotics (cs.RO) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions experiments in a Markov environment, which can be related to cybernetics (cs.CY).
